5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 4 | T-004 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-013 | — | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 5 | T-005 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-014 | — | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 6 | T-006 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-015 | — | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 7 | T-007 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-016 | — | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 8 | T-008 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-017 | — | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 9 | T-009 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-018 | — | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 10 | T-010 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-019 | — | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 1 | T-001 | Implement buffer-management protocol: `OnSamplerLoad(record)` allocates scsynth buffer + reads WAV; `OnSamplerFree` releases buffer; LRU eviction at 64-buffer cap. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-010 | — | - `tools/senseweave/sampler_buffers.py` exposes `BufferPool(scsynth_client, capacity=64)` with `acquire(record) -> bufnum`, `release(record)`, `evict_lru()`<br/>- WAV file path → `/b_allocRead bufnum path 0 -1` over OSC<br/>- LRU eviction triggered automatically when `acquire` exceeds capacity<br/>- on scsynth restart, pool detects buffer-id reuse failure and rebuilds<br/>- tests with a mock OSC client verify allocate, evict, release, and reuse paths |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 2 | T-002 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCS-011 | — | - SynthDef `sw_sampler_fx` reads from a stereo bus and writes to master bus<br/>- args: `delay_time` (sec, default 0.5), `delay_feedback` (0..0.85, default 0.55), `verb_mix` (default 0.35), `room_size` (default 0.7), `freeze_amount` (0..1, default 0.0), `comb_b_amount` (0..1, default 0.25), `comb_b_freq` (default 61.74)<br/>- bus number conventionally 16 (stereo, so 16+17)<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test verifies non-silent output for a known impulse input and frequency-domain check that 61.74 Hz comb peak is present when `comb_b_amount > 0` |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 3 | T-003 | Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-012 | — | - `dispatch_sample(record, intent, *, position, position_rate, grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose, amp, fx_send) -> SamplerHandle` issues `/b_allocRead` (if needed), `/s_new sw_sampler ...` and returns a handle for later `/n_set gate 0` release<br/>- correlates `record.gain_db` with `amp`<br/>- handles per-mode effects presets (delay_time / verb_mix / freeze / comb_b vary by mode)<br/>- tests with mock OSC client verify correct bundle ordering, gate-release path, and per-mode preset application |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 4 | T-004 | Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-013 | — | - `sampler_dispatch.play_sampler(record, duration_sec, **params)` schedules a fire-and-forget grain cloud with an internal envelope of `duration_sec`<br/>- `start_sampler` / `stop_sampler` returns/uses a handle for sustained sampler voices that match the bowed/pad lifecycle<br/>- both code paths feed through the same `dispatch_sample` core<br/>- tests verify both lifecycles and that they can run concurrently without buffer-id collision |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 5 | T-005 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-014 | — | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 6 | T-006 | Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-015 | — | - daemon opens two JACK ports `cypherclaw-capture:in_contact` and `cypherclaw-capture:in_room`<br/>- each maintains a 60-second numpy ring buffer at 48 kHz<br/>- exposes `get_window(source, duration_sec, offset_sec) -> np.ndarray` for the moment-detector to pull recent windows<br/>- handles JACK xruns gracefully (logs, does not crash)<br/>- tests with a synthetic JACK input fixture verify ring-buffer correctness, window extraction, and xrun recovery |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 7 | T-007 | Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-016 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::InterestingMomentDetector` pulls 1-second windows every 250 ms<br/>- flags a window when: `spectral_flux > 0.6 * recent_median` AND `rms > -45 dBFS` AND `transient_count >= 2` AND `since_last_capture > 30 sec`<br/>- on flag, expands to a 4–8 second window centered on the flagged sub-window (length proportional to spectral richness)<br/>- thresholds are tunable via env / config<br/>- tests with canned audio fixtures (silence, footsteps, dishwasher hum, music) verify expected flag/no-flag for each |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 8 | T-008 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCS-017 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; narrow-band high-centroid → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"metallic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sustained\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; transient_density>3/sec → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"percussive\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"harmonic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 9 | T-009 | Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-018 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::save_capture(window, source, tags) -> SampleRecord` writes WAV with filename pattern `<source>_<YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ>_<arc>_<sampleid>.wav`<br/>- WAV is 24-bit PCM, 48 kHz, peak-normalized to -1 dBFS unless `peak < -30 dBFS` in which case raw is preserved<br/>- record inserted into `index.sqlite` with `gain_db` set to the normalization adjustment<br/>- tests verify file presence, format (24/48), peak-normalize behavior, and DB row |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 10 | T-010 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-019 | — | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n **Spr