\\\n+- Samples with `pitch_confidence < 0.4` or `pitch_hz <= 0` return 0 semitones, correctly playing \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"atonally\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Tests cover known pitch/key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and octave wrap shortest-path selection.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation leverages `harmonic_planner.py` for canonical key normalization and scale definitions, ensuring consistency with the rest of the SenseWeave harmony engine. The coding style and test patterns match the existing codebase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+No security vulnerabilities were identified. The implementation uses standard math libraries and does not involve unsafe operations or credential handling.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The code is concise, well-documented, and follows idiomatic Python patterns. The tests are comprehensive and use appropriate fixtures (standard within the project). Mandatory hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` were found to be already addressed in the daemon startup flows (`daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- [x] (Minor/Environmental) `pytest tests/ -x` encountered a `PermissionError` in `test_daemon_fallback.py` due to macOS Seatbelt restrictions on `~/.promptclaw/pets.json`. This is an environmental constraint unrelated to the T-019 changes. Focused tests for the new implementation (`tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py`) passed successfully.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation is solid and integrates well with the established harmonic planning utilities. No further actions required for this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+codex\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+I found the existing verifier output saved 