an.\\\\n-\\\\n-## T-011@20260502T001347Z Exploration Findings\\\\n-\\\\n-- Read `AGENTS.md`, `prd-cypherclaw-narrative-http-service.md`, `sdp/implementation-plan.md`, `sdp/task-graph.md`, Deniable's `deniable_narrative_integration_v1.md`, and Deniable's `world_bridge.py`; the relevant requirement is CN-005, `POST /beats/next`.\\\\n-- The existing `cypherclaw.narrative_api` pattern is a FastAPI `create_app(...)` factory with injected test doubles, lazy deploy-side imports, narrow request schemas, auth dependencies on protected endpoints, and helper modules that normalize flexible engine return shapes.\\\\n-- The deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.engine.NarrativeEngine` package is not present in this PromptClaw checkout, so tests must inject a fake engine and the default production path must report HTTP 503 when that package is absent.\\\\n-- The StoryBeat shape is owned by the narrative engine. Deniable's bridge requires `id`, `cycle_number`, and `arc_position` while preserving the full raw payload, so this endpoint should serialize the in-process beat without adding null/default fields from an over-constrained response schema.\\\\n-- The generated hardening bullets about SenseWeave self-critique/resource-governor wiring and daemon identity startup are outside this endpoint's affected area. Startup identity remains covered by `tests/test_narrative_api_main.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py`; no new dependencies or migrations are required for T-011.\\\\n-\\\\n-## T-011@20260502T001347Z Verification\\\\n-\\\\n-- Red phase confirmed before implementation: `pytest tests/test_narrative_api_beats.py -q` failed with `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'cypherclaw.narrative_api.beats'`.\\\\n-- Endpoint and existing narrative API tests passed: `pytest tests/test_narrative_api_beats.py tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py tests/test_narrative_api_events.py tests/test_narrative_api_health.py tests/test_narrative_api_main.py -q` reported `4